        action storyIntroductionDryRun;
        verification storyIntroductionDryRunDoD : Test { :>> id = "63940516-2c7d-4e8f-c142-51627384c002"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::demo; :>> procedureText = "D0093 first-value UX: walked the `introduction` skill's 5 steps on a fresh `keel init` project (init_smoke proves init+validate+guard, not the onboarding flow). FINDINGS + FIXES: (1) .engine/docs/tracking-template.sysml — the canonical authoring template a newcomer copies — had DUPLICATE `:>> id` lines on 3 example items (exampleBrief/exampleNeed/exampleDecision, a migration leftover); removed the stale first id of each (kept the placeholder 3f1c9a2e-* ids). (2) a fresh scaffold shipped NO .tracking/actors.sysml, so the newcomer's FIRST recorded fact (any createdBy/judgedBy) FAILED the actors guard (D0037) with 'unknown actor' — there was nothing to reference; added STARTER_ACTORS (a `you : Person` + `ai : Actor` placeholder registry) written by cmd_init, and init_smoke asserts it ships. VERIFIED the loop on a fresh project: authored a backlog action def + task -> orient (1 ready) -> append-result (write API) -> orient (1 done); after the actors fix, judgedBy=ai PASSES guard actors. CONFIRMED the skill's step 4 (full sprint ceremony) is load-bearing — closing a task without a delivery sprint trips sprint-coverage (by design, D0064). VERIFY: clippy --workspace --all-targets -D warnings green; cargo test 48 lib + init_smoke (+ the new actors assertion) + BDD pass; repo keel validate 155 + guard all (13) green; the kernel validate_instances re-checks the corrected template in pre-commit."; }
        part storyIntroductionDryRunDoDR1 : TestResult { :>> id = "63940516-2c7d-4e8f-c142-51627384c003"; :>> outcome = VerdictKind::pass; :>> judgedAgainst = "7bd115f"; :>> judgedAt = "2026-06-23"; :>> judgedBy = "claudeOpus"; }
    }

